intern experience

Beijing Community Radius Information Technology Co., Ltd.

Learn java backend development, MySQL database read and write, write Spring Boot port, and finally use the above methods to independently design a system login interface, which can verify whether the login information is correct from the cloud database, and count the number of logins by different users. 1 mont's internship

French National Centre for Scientific Research Satie

Processing laser vibration signals by probability and statistical methods (MATLAB signal processing, designing a Fourier frequency domain filters to accurately extract useful signals from 3D vibration data obtained by the PSV500 laser vibrometer, using prony method to find the pole signal, analyzing the phase velocity of the vibration through the pole. 3 months of internship, highly recognized by Professor Roger REYNAUD, the internship code has been open sourced on my GitHub)

Project experience

2019-

Pololu Robot Soccer Battle

This is a continuous project, the task is to adjust and improve the entire project based on the previous two students. I serve as the leader of the group. We used OpenCV for image processing, ZigBee for networking, and Mbed data processing to realize the robot's autonomous ball passing operation. Under the surveillance of a webcam, a computer as the host is responsible for real-time communication with the two robots via Bluetooth, controlling their position, angle, and speed. Another program monitors the position of the ball in real time and synchronizes the information to the host , The host sends instructions to control the two robots to reach the appropriate position at the right angle and speed to achieve the pass. The project lasts 6 months and the code has been open sourced on GitHub

Space invader

Develop "Space Invader". The game's interface contains players, invaders, missiles and other elements, independently design the game logic, design different levels, set the winning and ending logic. Game rules: players can move up, down, left, and right, and can launch missiles; intruders can move left and right, and randomly launch missiles; players need to use missiles to destroy all invaders within a specified time, while ensuring that they are not attacked. When the game is completed without being hit, the player wins. This is a complete game that has been open sourced on GitHub

Interactive interface design

Using Microsoft's basic class library to develop the robot interactive interface, the difficulty of this program is to rewrite the Sleep function, so that the data in the listbox can be displayed line by line. This is a semi-finished product that will be used as a control interface for future robots. Third-party program interfaces are now open. Open sourced on GitHub. In addition, this program also has a qt version, written using qt4.8.7. This program calls two timer threads, which can run two different operations separately and time them. Open source on GitHub

In addition, I also tried to write some other applications using mfc, such as a document editor Editor with an open third-party application program interface, a multi-window game that can call files of different formats in different windows, a Backgammon game and so on. They are all open source on GitHub.

Repair and color old photos

Using the GAN algorithm, the Tesla T4 graphics card provided by colab, a variety of different tools to fit the blurred human face, eliminate the creases of the photo, and color the black and white photo

Fragmented image matching

This project was completed by a team. The main part I am responsible for is image feature point matching. Using the FAST and Brisk algorithms that come with OpenCV, I find the position and rotation angle of the fragments in the whole picture, and automatically stitch the fragments to the picture in. This project is mainly used in the field of cultural relics restoration and intelligent picture recognition. Open sourced on GitHub

Intelligent image cutting based on seam carving algorithm

When cutting the image, this algorithm can automatically identify the main objects in the picture, keep the shape of the main objects unchanged as much as possible, and cut off the surrounding parts. This algorithm is especially applicable when you need to crop a photo and you don't want the object to deform, such as when making a PPT, writing a report, and so on.

Optical flow

This project is mainly used to identify moving objects in the video and determine the direction and speed of the object's movement. The algorithm compares the "mean-standard deviation" method with the "sigma-delta" method to extract the difference in the effects of moving objects, and uses the latter to output optical flow. Open sourced

DirectX exploration

GPU programming using DirectX for faster 3D image fitting. The difficulty of this project is to separate the coordinate system. The DirectX model gives a coordinate system centered on the object, and the angle we look at by pressing the keys, whitch can also be understood as the camera's position. The Earth-Moon system requires a global center, and the angle of the Earth-Moon system can be changed by pressing the button. The project later added two more cars and repeatedly called functions to make the glass transparent. Later, a moving character model was added. The purpose of the project is to learn DirectX. Open sourced

Mandebrotu

This project compares the effects of single-threaded, partitioned multi-threaded, progressive multi-threaded, OpenMP and other forms on the calculation speed under different versions of the compiler, and added the intrinsic function at the end, using the AVX instruction set and YMM 256-bit register weight I wrote a function for calculation, which increased the calculation speed from the initial 8-13 seconds to 40 milliseconds. Open sourced

2020-

Android APP: Don't forget things

The to-do list APP is a simple memo. This APP is a lightweight APP with a simple interface and clear operation. Part of the mqtt network server code will be added later to implement the online backup function. The main interface of the APP has only one input box, and the Enter key is the confirmation key. Click on each to-do event to edit the details, press and hold to mark it as completed, and press and hold again to delete it. It has been listed on the Huawei application market. Project address: https://github.com/zijian-rayan/todo-List

Android APP：Planning Ploytech Paris Saclay

This is a timetable app. It is a simple webview-based app that makes it easier to view the school's timetable website without having to enter the browser every time. Since my classmates complained to me that the schedule website was being unavailable, but after reviewing it, I found out that the classmate's browser did not give the cookie write and send permissions, which made it impossible to login to the website. The APP solves the difficulty of viewing the timetable for Android users once and for all. This app adds the permission of cookies, the volume is only 1.8M, and the target user is all Android 7.0 and above devices. It has been listed on the Huawei application market. Project address: https://github.com/zijian-rayan/MyPage

Android APP：Let’s Maze

This is a maze game using the gravity sensing of a mobile phone. It is divided into five levels. The general rules are as follows: The initial position is where the red square is. We need to shake the mobile phone to move the red square to the green square. This is the end point. If you accidentally touch the yellow dot, game over. The purpose of this game design is to systematically learn Android development, to understand the writing and reading rules of memory, to learn to apply the sensors of mobile phones, and to use various plug-ins. Because the review of games in China is very complicated, this app has not been listed anywhere, but you can download the experience on GitHub. Project address: https://github.com/zijian-rayan/Maze

Android APP：MAXREFDES

The APP is modified based on MAXREFDES100_Android_SRC. The APP mainly adds the mqtt server access function on this basis, and sends data to the server in real time, which is then obtained and evaluated by the workstation. This project uses the MAXREFDES100 #: HEALTH SENSOR PLATFORM health platform. The main purpose is to remotely monitor the user's health. The project is not yet complete. Test project address: https://github.com/zijian-rayan/MQTTClient

.NET Mail client

This is a mail sending and receiving software based on the .NET framework, which uses SMTP and POP3 protocols to capture and send mail. In the project, I used the TreeNode structure to store mail, and only synced the latest 30 mails at a time. In the software, I have realized uploading and downloading attachments, and can display the contents of the email in different formats (HTML or PlanTex). Project is open source
